<p>How to format a price according to a local code (i.e. en_GB, en_AG , de_DE). Preferably with angular.</p>  <p>Example :</p>  <pre><code>{{4950.00|localCurrency:en_GB}} : displays : £4,950.00  {{4950.00|localCurrency:it_IT}} : displays : 4.950,00€  {{4950.00|localCurrency:fr_FR}} : displays : 4 950,00€ </code></pre>  <p>Please note that Angular's</p>  <pre><code>{{myCurrencyValue | currency:'XXX'}}  </code></pre>  <p>does <strong><em>not</em></strong> do exactly what is asked here.</p>